answer.text: "Our group of 6 did the intermediate trip. It was the first time white water rafting for 5 of us. The guides did a great job explaining everything about what to wear, what to expect, and safety precautions. We took the time before getting in the water to practice paddling and the different commands. On one of the rapids, 4 of us ended up falling into the water. It was a really scary experience but our guide was quick on his feet and strong to save us all and pull us back into the boat.  Even though we fell in, I would do it again with liquid descent. It was a fun experience and the scenery was beautiful. Also the guys were super attractive so that was nice"

answer.text: "An extension of the 16th Street Mall, I crossed this pedestrian bridge (going over Valley Highway) and unwittingly ended up in the Highland neighborhood. I spent my first afternoon in Denver aimlessly rambling about and passed a lot of time in the green spaces along the South Platte River.  The Highland Bridge is an attractive architectural piece, which is beautiful enough to warrant taking photos of it. From here you get a fun vantage point to capture views of Denver too. If you are exploring Denver on foot (which you should), make a point to check out all the parks and pedestrian bridges near the South Platte River.  [#Yelp365: 61/365]"
